  "body": "Checking the [Dockerfile](https://github.com/hyperledger/besu/blob/master/docker/openjdk-11/Dockerfile) seems that base image `openjdk:11.0.7-jre-slim-buster` is bringing some vulnerabilities flagged by some image scanning tools like snyk or harbor.\r\n\r\nTo get list of vulnerabilities you can run following command:\r\n\r\n```\r\n docker scan -f docker/openjdk-11/Dockerfile hyperledger/besu:develop-openjdk-11 --severity high\r\n```\r\n\r\nProducing following output:\r\n```\r\nTested 91 dependencies for known issues, found 21 issues.\r\n\r\nBase Image                      Vulnerabilities  Severity\r\nopenjdk:11.0.7-jre-slim-buster  77               21 high, 13 medium, 43 low\r\n```\r\n\r\nIn addition some alternative base images are recommended:\r\n\r\n```\r\nRecommendations for base image upgrade:\r\n\r\nAlternative image types\r\nBase Image                         Vulnerabilities  Severity\r\nopenjdk:16-ea-29-jdk-oraclelinux8  0                0 high, 0 medium, 0 low\r\nopenjdk:17-ea-6-jdk                0                0 high, 0 medium, 0 low\r\nopenjdk:16-ea-oracle               0                0 high, 0 medium, 0 low\r\nopenjdk:16-ea-15-jdk-oraclelinux8  0                0 high, 0 medium, 0 low\r\n```\r\n\r\nIt is not critical but some private docker registry won't allow to pull such images with high severity vulnerabilities.\r\n",
